- **exact-ns-unavoidable-spectator-couplings.md** — Exact NS activates the full projected triad network plus mirror-mode bookkeeping, so Tao's desired channels do not come alone. After the definition gate, the stress test is exact: write the desired / internal-leakage / external-leakage ledger on a minimal helical support and see whether any adversarially favorable helicity choice can keep leakage genuinely subordinate. [CHECKED]

### Vortex Stretching Slack (E003, adversarial E008)
- **adversarial-minimum-vs-slack.md** — Anti-parallel vortex tubes at sigma=2.5 achieve converged minimum VS slack of 157.70x (N=128), 34% below Taylor-Green vortex's 236.90x. Bowl-shaped sigma-dependence. Five-IC comparison. Near-Re-independent (157-175x across Re=100-1000). **E008: Protas-type PDE-optimized ICs (JFM 2020) not tested — strongest untested challenge.** [COMPUTED, CHECKED]
- **vortex-stretching-structural-slack.md** — The 158x minimum slack is a **lower bound over tested ICs** (NOT irreducible). Two sources: Holder step (S-omega misalignment) and Ladyzhenskaya step (extremizer mismatch). 3-factor decomposition (63% Lad, 31% geom, 6% sym) is **tautological by construction** but correctly identifies Ladyzhenskaya as dominant bottleneck. **E008: Protas ICs untested; domain-size dependent; decomposition TGV-specific.** [CHECKED, CONJECTURED]
- **beltrami-zero-vortex-stretching.md** — ABC flow (Beltrami: omega=u) has VS=0 identically at all times by incompressibility. Z-invariant vortex tubes also have VS=0 due to strain-vorticity orthogonality. Breaking z-symmetry (sinusoidal modulation) restores nonzero VS. [COMPUTED]

### Spectral Ladyzhenskaya Analysis (E006, adversarial E008)
- **spectral-ladyzhenskaya-negative-result.md** — Spectral support alone CANNOT improve sharp Ladyzhenskaya constant as worst-case bound. LP cross terms dominate (63% for Kolmogorov). Phase-optimized fields achieve near-sharp constants. **E008: phase optimization may be stuck in local optima (L-BFGS-B on non-convex landscape); Bernstein inequality offers alternative interpolation path.** Verdict: INCONCLUSIVE (directionally correct, not rigorous). [COMPUTED, CHECKED]
- **gaussian-effective-ladyzhenskaya.md** — In the Gaussian random-phase regime (CLT), C_{L,eff} = 3^{1/4}(||f||/||∇f||)^{3/4}. For Kolmogorov spectra: C_{L,eff} ≈ 1.707 × Re^{-3/8}. TYPICAL-case only, not a bound. [COMPUTED, CHECKED]
- **divergence-free-flatness-reduction.md** — Factor (5/9)^{1/4} ≈ 0.8633 (~13.7%) reduction. **E008 CORRECTION: NOT about div-free constraint — is purely vector-vs-scalar Gaussian effect (chi-squared moment). Numerically confirmed: div-free and non-div-free give identical flatness. Misattributed. Applies only to Gaussian fields, not actual NS flows. Mathematically trivial.** [VERIFIED but WEAKENED]

### BKM Enstrophy Theorem and Timescale Comparison (S002-E002/E004)
- **bkm-enstrophy-theorem-l4-proof.md** — **NEW (S002-E004).** Elementary 4-step proof: dE/dt ≤ sqrt(2)*||omega||_{L^inf}*E - nu*||grad omega||^2. All steps verified analytically and numerically. Key feature: no CZ theory needed (L4 interpolation + exact ||S||_{L2} = ||omega||_{L2}/sqrt(2) identity). PARTIALLY KNOWN — novelty is pedagogical, not discovery. Exposes the **logical circle**: regularity ↔ BKM ↔ enstrophy bounded — no enstrophy approach breaks it without controlling ||omega||_{L^inf}. Confidence: verified. Defensibility: 4/5. [VERIFIED]
- **re3-blowup-time-comparison.md** — **NEW (S002-E004).** T_BKM/T_Lad ~ Re^3: Ladyzhenskaya ODE has nu^{-3} factor (from Young's inequality) that BKM avoids. Verified numerically: T_Lad * Re^3 = 1.252e-3 = const across Re. **WEAKENED by adversarial**: compares different time types (finite blow-up vs exponential doubling) — apples-to-oranges. Confidence: provisional. Defensibility: 3/5. [COMPUTED, WEAKENED]
- **bgw-3d-obstruction.md** — **NEW (S002-E004).** BGW estimate fails in 3D for H^1 fields: requires H^{5/2}, not H^1. C ≤ 0.81 from DNS is a spectral dealiasing artifact. Motivated switch to L4 approach. Confidence: verified. [NEGATIVE RESULT]

### BKM Advantage and Alternative Criteria (E007, adversarial E008)
- **bkm-near-tightness-226x-advantage.md** — BKM bound tighter than Ladyzhenskaya. **E008 WEAKENED: comparison is apples-to-oranges (different quantities); 1.05x slack is circular (empirical C_BKM); with theoretical constant, advantage is ~80x not 226x; BKM tightness is Calderon-Zygmund theory, not NS-specific; doesn't transfer to regularity theory (requires L^inf control).** Direction correct, headline number misleading. Confidence: provisional. [COMPUTED, WEAKENED]
- **bmo-kozono-taniuchi-criterion.md** — BMO/L^inf ratio ~0.25-0.27 for TGV at Re=100-5000. Kozono-Taniuchi criterion ~4x tighter. **E008: INCONCLUSIVE — ball sampling underestimates BMO; single IC; limited Re; "universality" unsupported with 4 data points.** [NOVEL but methodologically limited] Confidence: provisional.
- **vorticity-intermittency-measures.md** — Vorticity flatness F4 = 2-12x Gaussian at all Re. C_{L,eff}/C_L ~ F4^{-0.30}. Explains WHY Ladyzhenskaya is loose. [COMPUTED] — **Most defensible finding per E008 claims ranking.**
- **conditional-vortex-stretching-bound.md** — Conjectured: C(F4) ≈ 0.003/F4. **S002-E004: C_Leff^4 = F4*R^3 identity is an exact tautology — C(F4) correlation is an artifact (mediated by R). Research direction KILLED.** **E008: INCONCLUSIVE — purely empirical, single IC, narrow F₄ range, no proof F₄ bounded.** [CONJECTURED, KILLED]

### Geometric Regularity and Beltrami Structure (vasseur-pressure E006)
- **geometric-regularity-criteria.md** — **NEW (E006).** Survey of geometric regularity criteria (Constantin-Fefferman 1993, Beirao da Veiga-Berselli 2002, Vasseur 2007): smoothness of vorticity/velocity direction implies regularity. For Beltrami flows, vorticity direction = velocity direction, so these criteria become identical. Holder-1/2 is the best exponent known. [VERIFIED]
- **beltrami-pressure-analytical.md** — **NEW (E006).** Exact derivation: Beltrami flows have L = omega x u = 0, so p = -|u|^2/2 + const (Bernoulli). CZ loss is exactly zero. **E009: mechanism correct, practical significance uncertain — exact Beltrami trivially regular; near-Beltrami needs quantitative ||L|| -> beta bound (open analytical problem).** Grade B+. [VERIFIED]
- **near-beltrami-pressure-perturbation.md** — **NEW (E006), UPDATED (E007, E009, E010).** For u = u_B + eps v, Lamb vector and bad pressure are O(eps). Key obstacle (truncation) RESOLVED by E007. **E009: mechanism has discontinuous character at analytical level. E010: definitively confirmed — even eps=0.01 destroys B_k decay; beta > 1 only for eps < ~0.02.** Conditional regularity conjecture: may hold but epsilon_0 must be extremely small. [VERIFIED]
- **near-beltrami-negative-result.md** — **NEW (E010).** Definitive negative result: Beltrami-De Giorgi mechanism does NOT generalize to near-Beltrami flows. Perturbed-ABC sweep (eps=0.01 to 0.5): B_k decay destroyed for any eps > 0, Bernoulli dominance lost for eps >= 0.05, beta_eff degrades continuously (no threshold). Leray projection is minor correction (16% at k=1, <0.4% at k>=5). Mechanism applies to measure-zero set of exact curl eigenstates only. [COMPUTED]

### Vasseur De Giorgi Framework (vasseur-pressure E001, E003, E004, E005, E008)
- **[vasseur-de-giorgi/](vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md)** — Vasseur's 2007 De Giorgi approach to NS regularity. Beta is a recurrence exponent (NOT pressure integrability). Beta > 3/2 implies full regularity (Conjecture 14). Current beta < 4/3, bottleneck is a single non-divergence pressure term `P_k^{21}`. DNS measurement approaches defined and TESTED. DNS results: all beta_eff < 4/3 (max 1.01 for ABC); bottleneck exponent gamma DECREASES with Re (gap is genuine); ABC/Beltrami flow uniquely favorable. CZ slack for `P_k^{21}` is k-INDEPENDENT (FALSIFIES CZ improvement hypothesis). `P21` has LESS CZ slack than full pressure. Tran-Yu Galilean invariance program ORTHOGONAL. Pressure Poisson equation Galilean-invariant for div-free flows. Choi-Vasseur 2014 three-way decomposition (beta=7/6, does NOT bypass bottleneck). Post-2007 landscape: NO paper has improved beta beyond 4/3. Fernandez-Dalgo 2025 dynamic pressure (epsilon-regularity, not De Giorgi). Vasseur-Yang 2021 vorticity De Giorgi: pressure eliminated, but universal 4/3 barrier from trilinear form. H^1 pressure route structurally dead. **E009: adversarial review of 6 claims.** **S2-E001: Proposition 3 sharpness audit — Chebyshev on NS solutions is single improvable step.** **S2-E003: Universal formula beta = 1 + s/n across 9 model PDEs; Chebyshev NOT independently improvable (6 routes ruled out or circular); SQG success = drift structure, not Chebyshev; div-free level-set question RESOLVED by S2-E008 (constant field extremizer — no improvement). S2-E004: Compensated compactness / commutator route CLOSED — three-layer obstruction (no div-curl, commutator remainder dominance, CRW vacuous); SQG-NS structural gap; beta = 4/3 sharp within energy+Sobolev+CZ+Chebyshev class. S2-E002: DNS level-set distribution tails IC-dependent (TG p~10, Random p~8-9, ABC p~2.1 < 10/3); Chebyshev tightness ratios ~3-5x and k-independent (constant slack, not beta-improving). S2-E005: Frequency-localized De Giorgi via LP decomposition CLOSED — Bernstein exchange rate 2^{3j/5} is dimensional, CZ is optimal frequency-by-frequency estimate, LP gives 5-10x worse bounds; paraproduct transition (resonance at low k, paraproduct at high k); direction 2 closed. S2-E006: Non-CZ pressure routes (IBP beta=1, H^1/BMO beta=4/3, CRW beta<=1) — beta=4/3 TOOL-INDEPENDENT, locked to NS quadratic structure; CZ consolidation gain exactly 1/3; 12 published approaches surveyed, none beat 4/3; 3 remaining directions. S2-E007: Adversarial review confirms obstruction — all 7 closures survive attack, 3 combination attacks fail, 15-paper lit search + Vasseur 2025 confirms no improvement, Tao 2016 supercritical connection; novel claim rankings (Claim 3 seven-route obstruction most significant); SDP formalization top priority. S2-E008: Chebyshev bound PROVABLY TIGHT for div-free fields — constant field u=(c,0,0) achieves ratio->1; all 4 De Giorgi chain steps individually tight; beta = 4/3 SHARP (rigorous); div-free level-set question RESOLVED (no improvement); SDP unnecessary. far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole exploration-001: exact obstruction reconstruction — harmonic `P_{k1}` is already favorable; the surviving far-field loophole is a decomposition mismatch, not literal `P_{k21}`; any live route must show an alternative near/far split makes the pressure factor `U_k`-dependent.** **29 entries.**

