+
+- the carrier scale `a1`,
+- the slow clock `a2`,
+- the amplifier channel `a2 a3 -> a3`,
+- the conduit `a4`,
+- the output witness `a5`.
+
+[COMPUTED] Because that preferred object still contains the monomial core
+
+```text
+a1^2 -> a2,
+a1^2 -> a3,
+a2 a3 -> a3,
+```
+
+the predecessor singleton non-embeddability result applies immediately. So there is no fresh faithful support to audit inside this strategy.
+
+[CHECKED] The only backup is packetized, and it remains non-canonical: support choice, projection choice, leakage bookkeeping, and exact-network restoration are not fixed by exact NS.
+
+So the correct mission outcome is not a firewall and not a hidden-trigger construction. It is outcome 4 from the strategy brief:
+
+```text
+no canonical faithful test object survives
+```
+
+## Direction Tried
+
+### 1. Phase 0 definition gate for a tiny delayed trigger
+
+[CHECKED] Exploration 001 asked whether narrowing the mission from "near-closed Tao circuit" to "tiny delayed trigger" actually produces a smaller theorem-facing exact object.
+
+[CHECKED] It does not. The trigger remains meaningful only through the full delayed-transfer chain. The faithful exact formulation is the inherited five-role helical hypergraph with trigger-centered observables on `a3`, not a new scalar or lower-role object.
+
+[CHECKED] The packetized backup fails the canonization gate immediately, so it cannot replace the inherited singleton object as one theorem target.
+
+[CHECKED] That is enough to stop the strategy without a separate Phase 1 or Phase 2 campaign.
+
+## Strongest Findings
+
+1. [VERIFIED] Tao's trigger variable is still the right mechanism-level reference object, but it is causally defined, not standalone.
+2. [CHECKED] A trigger-only exact object collapses back to the predecessor's five-role exact object once smallness, delay, visibility, leakage, and back-reaction are all made explicit.
+3. [COMPUTED] The predecessor singleton-support obstruction therefore transfers directly to the only faithful exact trigger object.
+4. [CHECKED] The packetized fallback still fails canonization, so there is no canonical replacement object.
+
+## Negative Results and Dead Ends
