+# Final Report: Strategy 001
+
+## Executive Verdict
+
+```text
+model-level negative: no canonical faithful test object
+```
+
+[CHECKED] The strategy's trigger-focused definition gate does not produce a new exact-NS object. The only faithful exact trigger object is the same five-role amplitude-level helical hypergraph already isolated in the predecessor near-closed-circuit mission, now with `a3` singled out as the trigger.
+
+[CHECKED] A genuinely smaller trigger-only object does not survive. To say the trigger is tiny before threshold yet dynamically decisive after threshold, one must also keep:
+
+- the carrier scale `a1`,
+- the slow clock `a2`,
+- the amplifier channel `a2 a3 -> a3`,
+- the conduit `a4`,
+- the output witness `a5`.
+
+[COMPUTED] Because that preferred object still contains the monomial core
+
+```text
+a1^2 -> a2,
+a1^2 -> a3,
+a2 a3 -> a3,
+```
+
+the predecessor singleton non-embeddability result applies immediately. So there is no fresh faithful support to audit inside this strategy.
+
+[CHECKED] The only backup is packetized, and it remains non-canonical: support choice, projection choice, leakage bookkeeping, and exact-network restoration are not fixed by exact NS.
+
+So the correct mission outcome is not a firewall and not a hidden-trigger construction. It is outcome 4 from the strategy brief:
+
+```text
+no canonical faithful test object survives
+```
+
+## Direction Tried
+
+### 1. Phase 0 definition gate for a tiny delayed trigger
+
+[CHECKED] Exploration 001 asked whether narrowing the mission from "near-closed Tao circuit" to "tiny delayed trigger" actually produces a smaller theorem-facing exact object.
+
+[CHECKED] It does not. The trigger remains meaningful only through the full delayed-transfer chain. The faithful exact formulation is the inherited five-role helical hypergraph with trigger-centered observables on `a3`, not a new scalar or lower-role object.
+
+[CHECKED] The packetized backup fails the canonization gate immediately, so it cannot replace the inherited singleton object as one theorem target.
+
+[CHECKED] That is enough to stop the strategy without a separate Phase 1 or Phase 2 campaign.
+
+## Strongest Findings
+
+1. [VERIFIED] Tao's trigger variable is still the right mechanism-level reference object, but it is causally defined, not standalone.
+2. [CHECKED] A trigger-only exact object collapses back to the predecessor's five-role exact object once smallness, delay, visibility, leakage, and back-reaction are all made explicit.
+3. [COMPUTED] The predecessor singleton-support obstruction therefore transfers directly to the only faithful exact trigger object.
+4. [CHECKED] The packetized fallback still fails canonization, so there is no canonical replacement object.
+
+## Negative Results and Dead Ends
+
+- [CHECKED] "Narrow to the trigger" is not a real object reduction. It keeps the same exact support and monomial structure while only changing which observables are emphasized.
+- [COMPUTED] No new minimal exact-support audit survives, because the inherited preferred object is already structurally dead.
+- [CHECKED] Packetization remains an underconstrained family, not a theorem-facing exact model.
+
+## Recommended Next Move For The Missionary
+
+[CHECKED] Kill this line as currently posed.
+
+[CHECKED] Only reopen it under a precursor mission whose primary job is:
+
+```text
+define and defend a canonical exact packet model for a Tao-style trigger
+before asking for either a firewall theorem or a hidden-trigger construction
+```
+
+[CHECKED] Without that, future work would again inherit the same fork:
+
+- the faithful exact singleton object is already dead,
+- the flexible packet object is still not canonical.
+
+## Claims Worth Carrying Forward
+
+- [CHECKED] A Tao-style trigger can be defined sharply only inside the full delayed-transfer role chain, not as an isolated exact scalar.
+- [COMPUTED] The predecessor singleton non-embeddability result is not just about the whole near-closed circuit; it already kills the only faithful exact trigger object that survives definition.
+- [CHECKED] For mechanism-narrowing missions, "does the narrowed question actually shrink the faithful exact object?" should be asked before any new exploration budget is spent.
